SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 31
BY SENATOR LUNEAU
A RESOLUTION
To commend and recognize Donald G. "Don" Kelly, former legislator and attorney, for his
distinguished public service and long-standing years of service to the people of
Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Donald G. "Don" Kelly, an attorney from Natchitoches Parish, has
devoted his life to service to his community, his clients, and the citizens of the state of
Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, a graduate of Northwestern State University, Don earned a Juris Doctor
degree from Louisiana State University, laying the foundation for a distinguished legal
career; and
WHEREAS, admitted to the Louisiana State Bar in 1966, Donald Kelly has practiced
law in this state with integrity, professionalism, and unwavering dedication for six decades;
and
WHEREAS, Don is admitted to practice law before the Supreme Court of the United
States, the United States Courts of Appeals for the Fifth and Eighth Circuits, and the United
States District Courts for the Eastern, Western, and Middle Districts of Louisiana, which
reflects the breadth and respect of his professional standing; and
WHEREAS, Don Kelly maintained active membership in the Louisiana State Bar
Association, the Natchitoches Parish Bar Association, the Louisiana Association for Justice,
and the American Association of Justice, and is a former president of the Louisiana
Association for Justice; and
WHEREAS, having no prior experience in politics, Don was elected as a delegate
for the 24th Representative District of the Constitutional Convention of 1973 and was
subsequently elected to the Louisiana Senate, serving from 1976 to 1996, representing his
constituents with professional diligence and distinction; and
