WHEREAS, during his tenure in the Senate, Don served on the Senate Committee
on Judiciary A, the Senate Committee on Judiciary B, the joint budget committee, the Senate
Committee on Natural Resources, and the Senate Committee on Finance, making significant
contributions during legislative deliberations affecting the people of Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, from 1980 to 1987, he served as chairman of the Senate Committee on
Transportation, Highways and Public Works providing steady leadership and oversight on
matters critical to the state's infrastructure and economic development; and
WHEREAS, recognized as a distinguished Senate floor leader for two terms under
Governor Edwin Edwards and for one term under Governor Buddy Roemer, Don
demonstrated bipartisan respect, leadership, and the confidence of his colleagues; and
WHEREAS, Don Kelly's public and professional career reflects a legacy of
principled public service, commitment to justice, and steadfast dedication to the betterment
of the people of Louisiana.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend and recognize Donald G. "Don" Kelly for his exemplary service as
a Louisiana State Senator and a distinguished member of the Louisiana Bar Association, and
does further express its sincere appreciation for his many contributions to the state of
Louisiana.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
Donald G. "Don" Kelly as an expression of the Louisiana Senate's highest regard and respect
and extends best wishes to Don for continued success and fulfillment.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
